WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:14.100
The Queen of New Orleans

00:14.100 --> 00:26.180
Part 1 The Queen is Crown

00:26.180 --> 00:35.180
New Orleans 1805

00:35.180 --> 00:39.180
Two hundred years ago New Orleans was quite a place to be

00:39.180 --> 00:43.180
Lots of interest in people lived there or passed through

00:43.180 --> 00:46.180
Musicians, gamblers, sailors

00:46.180 --> 00:49.180
Some nights the French Quarter of the city was

00:49.180 --> 00:57.180
Well let's say it was lively

00:57.180 --> 01:02.180
Down in Congo Square or Flatts Congo was the people there called it

01:02.180 --> 01:05.180
The scene was also pretty lively

01:05.180 --> 01:08.180
It was a place where freed slaves used to go

01:08.180 --> 01:11.180
A place where they worshiped a special kind of religion

01:11.180 --> 01:14.180
This religion had a lot of different names

01:14.180 --> 01:17.180
Backhand, Ifa or Isha

01:17.180 --> 01:22.180
Nowadays we call it Voodoo

01:22.180 --> 01:26.180
About that time there was a Voodoo Queen in New Orleans

01:26.180 --> 01:31.180
Her name was Sanite Debe and everyone was afraid of them

01:31.180 --> 01:34.180
Lots of people used to ask her for favors

01:34.180 --> 01:37.180
But she made a good living out of it

01:38.180 --> 01:42.180
What do you want?

01:42.180 --> 01:44.180
I need your help

01:44.180 --> 01:45.180
Oh yeah?

01:45.180 --> 01:48.180
I owe somebody a lot of money

01:48.180 --> 01:53.180
I want to know if you have anything that belongs to him

01:53.180 --> 01:56.180
Yes, I managed to get this from him

01:56.180 --> 02:01.180
Nice handkerchief, guess he must be pretty rich

02:01.180 --> 02:03.180
Yes he is

02:03.180 --> 02:06.180
How much do you owe him?

02:06.180 --> 02:08.180
$5,000

02:08.180 --> 02:11.180
Then you're one stupid son of a bitch

02:11.180 --> 02:13.180
It wasn't my fault

02:13.180 --> 02:15.180
This is going to cost you money

02:15.180 --> 02:17.180
I'll pay you what I can

02:17.180 --> 02:19.180
You'll pay me $500

02:19.180 --> 02:22.180
$500? I can't

02:22.180 --> 02:25.180
$500? Take it or leave it

02:25.180 --> 02:26.180
But I can't

02:26.180 --> 02:28.180
Okay, goodbye

02:28.180 --> 02:31.180
No, open the door, open the door

02:31.180 --> 02:33.180
I'll pay you $500

02:33.180 --> 02:35.180
Bring me half tomorrow

02:39.180 --> 02:44.180
Sanite Debe was the number one Voodoo woman in New Orleans

02:44.180 --> 02:47.180
But then, someone else came along

02:47.180 --> 02:50.180
This is the story of Marie LaVoe

02:50.180 --> 02:55.180
The woman who became the new Voodoo Queen of New Orleans

02:55.180 --> 02:57.180
At the beginning of our story

02:57.180 --> 03:00.180
Marie was just a simple hairdresser

03:01.180 --> 03:03.180
Marie? Marie?

03:03.180 --> 03:05.180
Hello Blanche

03:05.180 --> 03:08.180
Marie, do you have time to cut my hair today?

03:08.180 --> 03:10.180
Not now Blanche, no

03:10.180 --> 03:12.180
Maybe tomorrow?

03:12.180 --> 03:14.180
Okay, I'll see you tomorrow

03:14.180 --> 03:16.180
Fine, bye for now

03:20.180 --> 03:21.180
Well, hello

03:21.180 --> 03:24.180
Oh my god, you frightened me

03:24.180 --> 03:27.180
I can't see anything with the blinds down

03:27.180 --> 03:28.180
Who is it?

03:28.180 --> 03:31.180
Well Marie, don't you remember my voice

03:31.180 --> 03:34.180
Jacques, is it you?

03:34.180 --> 03:36.180
Show is

03:39.180 --> 03:42.180
What do you think you're doing sitting here in the dark?

03:42.180 --> 03:43.180
What do you want?

03:43.180 --> 03:46.180
Marie, what do you think I want?

03:46.180 --> 03:48.180
I don't know Jacques

03:48.180 --> 03:50.180
I'm not a mind reader

03:50.180 --> 03:54.180
Come on Marie, did you forget Friday night already?

03:54.180 --> 03:57.180
Friday night was Friday night, Jacques

03:57.180 --> 04:00.180
Today is another day

04:00.180 --> 04:04.180
And today could be another day like Friday Marie

04:11.180 --> 04:17.180
There was quite a party the day that Marie LaVoe and Jacques Paris got married

04:17.180 --> 04:19.180
Marie LaVoe

04:19.180 --> 04:22.180
Fine looking woman, intelligent

04:22.180 --> 04:24.180
And knew how to make an honest buck

04:24.180 --> 04:26.180
Jacques Paris

04:26.180 --> 04:30.180
Well, he was fine looking too but

04:30.180 --> 04:35.180
Well, let's say he wasn't a regular kind of guy, you know

04:35.180 --> 04:39.180
The kind that gets up in the morning and goes to work

04:39.180 --> 04:45.180
If he was up in the morning, it was because he'd been up all night drinking and gambling

04:45.180 --> 04:48.180
A lot of people were very surprised when Marie married someone

04:48.180 --> 04:50.180
Like Jacques

04:53.180 --> 05:00.180
And do you, Marie, take Jacques to be your lawful wedded husband?

05:00.180 --> 05:01.180
I do

05:01.180 --> 05:08.180
And do you, Jacques, take Marie to be your lawful wedded wife?

05:10.180 --> 05:11.180
Jacques

05:11.180 --> 05:12.180
Huh?

05:13.180 --> 05:20.180
Do you take this woman to be your lawful wedded wife?

05:20.180 --> 05:22.180
Oh sure, preacher man

05:22.180 --> 05:25.180
Jacques, just say I do

05:25.180 --> 05:27.180
Okay, I do

05:27.180 --> 05:32.180
Good, I now pronounce you man and wife, you may kiss the bride

05:32.180 --> 05:35.180
It's all right, Mr. preacher, I already did that

05:43.180 --> 05:48.180
Hey Marie, hi Blanche

05:48.180 --> 05:51.180
What's it like to be a married woman?

05:51.180 --> 05:53.180
When I find out, I'll tell you

05:57.180 --> 05:59.180
Hello, Jacques

05:59.180 --> 06:01.180
Well, hello

06:01.180 --> 06:03.180
Now, do I know you?

06:03.180 --> 06:05.180
You sure do

06:05.180 --> 06:07.180
Refresh my memory, pretty lady

06:07.180 --> 06:09.180
My name is Gina

06:09.180 --> 06:13.180
We met in Baton Rouge a year or so ago

06:13.180 --> 06:17.180
Ah, yes, very refreshing

06:17.180 --> 06:21.180
So, Jacques, you went and got yourself a wife

06:21.180 --> 06:23.180
I sure did

06:23.180 --> 06:26.180
Marion Marie LaVoe was the best thing I ever did

06:26.180 --> 06:29.180
You think so?

06:29.180 --> 06:33.180
Well, now, you trying to tell me something?

06:33.180 --> 06:38.180
Well, yes I am, but here ain't the right place to tell you

06:40.180 --> 06:45.180
Marie, what is it Blanche?

06:45.180 --> 06:48.180
I think you should go outside

06:48.180 --> 06:50.180
Why should I do that Blanche?

06:50.180 --> 06:52.180
I'm having a fine time here

06:52.180 --> 06:58.180
Right, and Jacques is having a fine time out the bank

07:02.180 --> 07:06.180
Oh, Jacques, it's so good to see you again

07:06.180 --> 07:09.180
The show is, come here

07:09.180 --> 07:10.180
Not here

07:10.180 --> 07:11.180
Where then?

07:11.180 --> 07:16.180
I have a room, second floor in a rooming house on Rose Street

07:16.180 --> 07:18.180
Number 21

07:18.180 --> 07:21.180
Why don't you come and see me there?

07:21.180 --> 07:23.180
Show thing

07:23.180 --> 07:25.180
There they are

07:25.180 --> 07:27.180
Oh my God

07:27.180 --> 07:29.180
Jesus, how do I get out of here?

07:29.180 --> 07:31.180
There's no way out of here except through the house

07:31.180 --> 07:32.180
Get behind the tree

07:32.180 --> 07:33.180
What?

07:33.180 --> 07:35.180
Get behind the tree

07:35.180 --> 07:38.180
Jacques, are you out here?

07:38.180 --> 07:39.180
Jacques?

07:39.180 --> 07:42.180
Well, I'm Marie

07:42.180 --> 07:44.180
You with someone, Jacques?

07:44.180 --> 07:46.180
Will someone show as hell not?

07:46.180 --> 07:48.180
I'm just taking the air

07:48.180 --> 07:51.180
There's someone here I know there is

07:51.180 --> 07:54.180
I think she's here

07:54.180 --> 07:57.180
Wow, I like all my hair you bitch

07:57.180 --> 08:00.180
You're calling me a bitch?

08:00.180 --> 08:01.180
Let go of me

08:01.180 --> 08:04.180
You come after my husband on my wedding day

08:04.180 --> 08:06.180
And you call me a bitch?

08:06.180 --> 08:08.180
Let go of me

08:08.180 --> 08:10.180
Get me one good reason why I should do that

08:10.180 --> 08:12.180
Stop it, let me go

08:12.180 --> 08:14.180
Okay, I'll let go of you

08:14.180 --> 08:16.180
You're crazy

08:16.180 --> 08:19.180
And now you're calling me names

08:19.180 --> 08:23.180
Don't you dare call me names

08:23.180 --> 08:25.180
Why you?

08:25.180 --> 08:28.180
Get up

08:28.180 --> 08:30.180
Don't get me again

08:30.180 --> 08:32.180
Are you trying to kill me or something?

08:32.180 --> 08:35.180
I'm not gonna touch you again, you piece of garbage

08:35.180 --> 08:38.180
But if you ever go near my husband again

08:38.180 --> 08:41.180
I really will kill you

08:41.180 --> 08:43.180
Now get out of here

08:43.180 --> 08:46.180
You're a mad woman, Marie Loveau

08:46.180 --> 08:48.180
You regret doing this

08:48.180 --> 08:50.180
Marie, are you okay?

08:50.180 --> 08:51.180
I'm fine, Blanche

08:51.180 --> 08:52.180
Do you need any help?

08:52.180 --> 08:53.180
No, go away

08:53.180 --> 08:55.180
I want to talk to Jacques alone

08:55.180 --> 08:58.180
Okay, but yell if you need me

08:58.180 --> 08:59.180
Okay

08:59.180 --> 09:01.180
Marie

09:01.180 --> 09:03.180
Don't talk, Jacques

09:03.180 --> 09:04.180
Just listen

09:04.180 --> 09:06.180
This is our wedding day

09:06.180 --> 09:09.180
And I've just found you with another woman

09:09.180 --> 09:11.180
Marie, we were just talking

09:11.180 --> 09:13.180
In fact, I was just telling

09:13.180 --> 09:15.180
Listen, you're my husband now

09:15.180 --> 09:19.180
And from now on, you do things the way I want them

09:19.180 --> 09:20.180
I was just...

09:20.180 --> 09:21.180
Huh?

09:21.180 --> 09:22.180
You hurt me, Jacques

09:22.180 --> 09:23.180
We're a man and wife

09:23.180 --> 09:26.180
And we do things my way

09:26.180 --> 09:29.180
Are you serious?

09:29.180 --> 09:32.180
We're gonna do things your way?

09:32.180 --> 09:33.180
That's right

09:33.180 --> 09:34.180
Uh-uh

09:34.180 --> 09:36.180
No one tells me what to do, Marie

09:36.180 --> 09:39.180
I'm a free man, remember?

09:39.180 --> 09:40.180
I ain't a slave

09:40.180 --> 09:43.180
If you think you got yourself a slave when you married me

09:43.180 --> 09:44.180
You're wrong

09:44.180 --> 09:47.180
It doesn't make no difference that we're married

09:47.180 --> 09:49.180
I'm gonna do things my way

09:49.180 --> 09:51.180
And no one is gonna stop me

09:51.180 --> 09:54.180
You're gonna do things your way

09:54.180 --> 09:56.180
I sure am

09:56.180 --> 09:58.180
And that includes seeing other women

09:58.180 --> 10:02.180
Marie, I will go where I want

10:02.180 --> 10:04.180
See who I want

10:04.180 --> 10:06.180
And do what I want

10:06.180 --> 10:10.180
And there ain't a damn thing you can do about it

10:10.180 --> 10:12.180
Oh, Jacques

10:12.180 --> 10:15.180
You should not have said that

10:15.180 --> 10:18.180
You really shouldn't have said that

10:18.180 --> 10:22.180
You have to learn never ever

10:22.180 --> 10:25.180
To make me angry

10:25.180 --> 10:27.180
Marie

10:27.180 --> 10:30.180
Are you okay?

10:30.180 --> 10:31.180
No, Blanche

10:31.180 --> 10:32.180
I'm not okay

10:32.180 --> 10:34.180
Where's Jacques?

10:34.180 --> 10:35.180
I don't know

10:35.180 --> 10:36.180
And I don't care

10:36.180 --> 10:38.180
Marie

10:38.180 --> 10:40.180
It's your wedding day

10:40.180 --> 10:42.180
You just got married

10:42.180 --> 10:45.180
And you don't know where your husband is

10:45.180 --> 10:47.180
And you don't care

10:47.180 --> 10:48.180
No, Blanche

10:48.180 --> 10:49.180
I don't

10:49.180 --> 10:52.180
Marie, what's happened to you?

10:52.180 --> 10:54.180
What do you mean?

10:54.180 --> 10:56.180
You look different

10:56.180 --> 10:58.180
Your eyes

10:58.180 --> 11:01.180
I don't know what's happened to me Blanche

11:01.180 --> 11:04.180
But I sure as hell feel different

11:04.180 --> 11:05.180
I feel

11:05.180 --> 11:07.180
Angry and

11:07.180 --> 11:08.180
I don't know

11:08.180 --> 11:10.180
I also feel strong

11:10.180 --> 11:12.180
From now on

11:12.180 --> 11:16.180
I'm not gonna take any nonsense from Jack or anyone

11:16.180 --> 11:18.180
And first of all

11:18.180 --> 11:22.180
I'm gonna take care of that little trap he was talking to

11:22.180 --> 11:24.180
You know her name?

11:24.180 --> 11:25.180
I...

11:25.180 --> 11:28.180
No, I don't know her name

11:28.180 --> 11:30.180
I think you do Blanche

11:30.180 --> 11:31.180
Tell me

11:31.180 --> 11:33.180
Marie, tell me

11:33.180 --> 11:37.180
I think her name is Gina Baptiste

11:37.180 --> 11:40.180
Do you know where she lives?

11:40.180 --> 11:42.180
No, really I don't

11:42.180 --> 11:45.180
Blanche, find out where she lives for me

11:45.180 --> 11:49.180
Okay, but Blanche don't try to tell me what to do

11:49.180 --> 11:51.180
It's too late for that

11:51.180 --> 11:53.180
Okay Marie

11:53.180 --> 11:56.180
I'll find out where she lives

11:58.180 --> 12:00.180
A few days later

12:00.180 --> 12:03.180
Gina was in her room at the room in house

12:04.180 --> 12:06.180
Who's there?

12:06.180 --> 12:08.180
Is that you, Jack?

12:08.180 --> 12:10.180
Jack?

12:10.180 --> 12:11.180
Jack?

12:11.180 --> 12:13.180
Are you...

12:13.180 --> 12:15.180
What the hell is...

12:15.180 --> 12:17.180
Oh!

12:17.180 --> 12:18.180
Help!

12:18.180 --> 12:19.180
Someone help me!

12:19.180 --> 12:21.180
What's going on up there?

12:21.180 --> 12:23.180
This is disgusting!

12:23.180 --> 12:25.180
What's all the fuss about?

12:25.180 --> 12:27.180
Did you see anyone coming up to my door?

12:27.180 --> 12:30.180
Lady, there's always people coming to your door

12:30.180 --> 12:32.180
Someone just knocked on my door

12:32.180 --> 12:34.180
Did you see anyone?

12:34.180 --> 12:36.180
Well, I saw a woman going up the stairs

12:36.180 --> 12:38.180
What did she look like?

12:38.180 --> 12:40.180
I didn't see her face

12:40.180 --> 12:42.180
Anyway, what you yelling about?

12:42.180 --> 12:43.180
Look!

12:44.180 --> 12:46.180
My log is...

12:46.180 --> 12:48.180
There's blood everywhere

12:48.180 --> 12:50.180
What is it?

12:50.180 --> 12:53.180
Well, it was an animal

12:53.180 --> 12:55.180
Chicken, I guess now it's just blood

12:55.180 --> 12:59.180
And feathers and bones and stuff

12:59.180 --> 13:01.180
And look at my door!

13:01.180 --> 13:03.180
There's blood on my door

13:03.180 --> 13:04.180
Oh my God!

13:04.180 --> 13:05.180
What is it?

13:05.180 --> 13:08.180
Someone wrote the letter M on your dog

13:08.180 --> 13:10.180
What does it mean?

13:10.180 --> 13:13.180
Lady, you ain't from New Orleans, are you?

13:13.180 --> 13:14.180
No!

13:14.180 --> 13:17.180
Why did they write M on my door?

13:17.180 --> 13:19.180
Don't you know nothing?

13:19.180 --> 13:21.180
It's the first letter of the word mort

13:21.180 --> 13:23.180
That's French

13:23.180 --> 13:25.180
It means death

13:25.180 --> 13:28.180
And it's written on your door in blood

13:28.180 --> 13:33.180
Man, someone just put a curse on you

13:36.180 --> 13:41.180
Of course, it was Marie who wrote the letter M in blood on Gina's door

13:41.180 --> 13:46.180
Afterwards, she went out into the street and ran in the direction of her house

13:46.180 --> 13:48.180
But she didn't make it

13:48.180 --> 13:53.180
I'm sorry, I didn't see you

13:53.180 --> 13:57.180
No, just hold on there, Ma

13:57.180 --> 14:00.180
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to run into you now

14:00.180 --> 14:02.180
If you don't mind, I'll just be going

14:02.180 --> 14:05.180
I said, hold on there

14:05.180 --> 14:08.180
And calm down

14:08.180 --> 14:11.180
Now, are you okay?

14:11.180 --> 14:12.180
I'm fine

14:12.180 --> 14:17.180
Mom, you have blood all over your hands and your clothes

14:17.180 --> 14:19.180
Oh my God

14:19.180 --> 14:22.180
I think you should tell me what's going on here

14:22.180 --> 14:25.180
No, take your hands off me and let me go

14:25.180 --> 14:28.180
Mom, maybe you don't know me

14:28.180 --> 14:30.180
But I can help you

14:30.180 --> 14:32.180
What are you talking about?

14:32.180 --> 14:33.180
Who are you?

14:33.180 --> 14:36.180
My name is John Bayou

14:36.180 --> 14:38.180
John Bayou?

14:38.180 --> 14:41.180
Yes, but around here

14:41.180 --> 14:45.180
People call me Dr. John

14:46.180 --> 14:48.180
Dr. John

14:48.180 --> 14:51.180
Oh Lord Jesus, you're a voodoo doctor

14:51.180 --> 14:56.180
Mom, I'm just a preacher in a church for freed slaves

14:56.180 --> 15:00.180
I don't really like the expression voodoo doctor

15:00.180 --> 15:03.180
But it's what you are, leave me alone

15:03.180 --> 15:05.180
I don't want to talk to you

15:05.180 --> 15:08.180
Mom, you look like you're in big trouble

15:08.180 --> 15:10.180
I don't want help from no voodoo doctor

15:10.180 --> 15:14.180
Now, you listen to me, you need help

15:14.180 --> 15:17.180
I can smell death on it

15:17.180 --> 15:19.180
I ain't killed no one

15:19.180 --> 15:22.180
Just calm down and listen

15:22.180 --> 15:27.180
Right now, I'm probably the only person in your lives

15:27.180 --> 15:30.180
Who can help you, now come with me

15:30.180 --> 15:32.180
Where? Where are you taking me?

15:32.180 --> 15:35.180
Just across the street

15:35.180 --> 15:37.180
Somewhere we can talk

15:37.180 --> 15:40.180
Across the street? To that bar?

15:40.180 --> 15:41.180
That's right

15:41.180 --> 15:43.180
I'm not going into a bar

15:43.180 --> 15:45.180
I'm a respectable woman

15:45.180 --> 15:48.180
A respectable married woman

15:48.180 --> 15:51.180
I know you're a respectable woman

15:51.180 --> 15:55.180
But you need to clean up and we need to talk

15:55.180 --> 15:58.180
You can't go anywhere looking like that

15:58.180 --> 16:00.180
Oh God

16:00.180 --> 16:04.180
There are people across the street who can help you

16:04.180 --> 16:06.180
Now let's go

16:11.180 --> 16:19.180
Here she is, Dr. John

16:19.180 --> 16:21.180
She's all cleaned up now

16:21.180 --> 16:22.180
Thank you, Celeste

16:22.180 --> 16:26.180
Anytime, Dr. Anything else I can do for you

16:26.180 --> 16:29.180
No, thank you, Celeste, you've been more than helpful

16:29.180 --> 16:34.180
Okay, well you know where I am if you need me

16:34.180 --> 16:36.180
I don't like it here

16:36.180 --> 16:38.180
People are looking at me

16:38.180 --> 16:40.180
Only in your imagination

16:40.180 --> 16:43.180
They all got plenty of other things to think about

16:43.180 --> 16:46.180
I want to say sorry

16:46.180 --> 16:49.180
I wasn't very nice to you

16:49.180 --> 16:51.180
You don't need to apologize

16:51.180 --> 16:56.180
You just need to tell me what's going on

16:56.180 --> 17:00.180
You could start by telling me your name

17:00.180 --> 17:03.180
My name is Marie Paris

17:03.180 --> 17:05.180
Marie Paris?

17:05.180 --> 17:08.180
A married to a man named Jack Paris

17:08.180 --> 17:10.180
Maybe you've heard of him?

17:10.180 --> 17:16.180
Oh my goodness, yes, everyone in New Orleans knows Jack about us

17:16.180 --> 17:19.180
I didn't realize he had such a fine look at why

17:19.180 --> 17:23.180
Well, we've only been married for a week or so

17:23.180 --> 17:24.180
But my...

17:24.180 --> 17:28.180
Jack is not an easy man to be married to

17:28.180 --> 17:32.180
Well, I'm sure you're right about that

17:32.180 --> 17:35.180
Mr. Bayou, this is not a laughing matter

17:35.180 --> 17:37.180
I've just done something terrible

17:37.180 --> 17:40.180
Okay, if you want me to help

17:40.180 --> 17:43.180
You have to tell me what happened

17:43.180 --> 17:48.180
Okay, there was a woman at our wedding party

17:48.180 --> 17:51.180
I didn't know her, I don't know how she got there

17:51.180 --> 17:54.180
Anyway, she knew my husband and...

17:54.180 --> 17:56.180
Yes...

17:56.180 --> 18:01.180
I think my husband was planning to see her, like, secretly

18:01.180 --> 18:04.180
I see, go on

18:04.180 --> 18:07.180
I went to the place where she lives and...

18:07.180 --> 18:09.180
And?

18:09.180 --> 18:12.180
What did you do, Marie?

18:12.180 --> 18:16.180
I drew the letter M on her door, in blood

18:16.180 --> 18:17.180
Ah...

18:17.180 --> 18:20.180
I just wanted to frighten her

18:20.180 --> 18:23.180
Right, well, I guess I can understand that

18:23.180 --> 18:25.180
But there's something else?

18:25.180 --> 18:26.180
What?

18:26.180 --> 18:29.180
Well, I waited to see what happened

18:29.180 --> 18:32.180
I sat on the stairs just above her room

18:33.180 --> 18:37.180
Well, I was sitting there, I started to imagine things

18:37.180 --> 18:39.180
I couldn't stop myself

18:39.180 --> 18:41.180
What did you imagine, Marie?

18:41.180 --> 18:45.180
I imagined that I was stabbing her, like, with a knife

18:45.180 --> 18:48.180
Well, you only imagined that

18:48.180 --> 18:51.180
I know, but she screamed

18:51.180 --> 18:52.180
She did what?

18:52.180 --> 18:53.180
She screamed

18:53.180 --> 18:55.180
I could hear her through the door

18:55.180 --> 18:57.180
I imagined stabbing her with a knife

18:57.180 --> 18:59.180
And I could hear her screaming

19:00.180 --> 19:02.180
Ah!

19:02.180 --> 19:03.180
Ah!

19:03.180 --> 19:04.180
Ah!

19:04.180 --> 19:05.180
Ah!

19:05.180 --> 19:07.180
I can't stop it anymore

19:07.180 --> 19:09.180
I've got to get out of here

19:12.180 --> 19:13.180
Hello, Gina

19:13.180 --> 19:14.180
You!

19:14.180 --> 19:15.180
It's you!

19:15.180 --> 19:18.180
What are you doing to me?

19:18.180 --> 19:20.180
I ain't doing nothing, Gina

19:20.180 --> 19:22.180
You're killing me

19:22.180 --> 19:25.180
I ain't putting a finger on you, Gina

19:25.180 --> 19:27.180
But you're gonna die

19:27.180 --> 19:28.180
I'm certain of that

19:28.180 --> 19:30.180
You're a bad woman

19:30.180 --> 19:32.180
And you deserve to die

19:32.180 --> 19:34.180
Stop it

19:34.180 --> 19:36.180
And let me out of here

19:36.180 --> 19:38.180
You ain't going nowhere you travel

19:38.180 --> 19:40.180
Let me out of here

19:40.180 --> 19:41.180
You ain't leaving

19:41.180 --> 19:43.180
I have to get out of here

19:43.180 --> 19:44.180
The window

19:44.180 --> 19:46.180
I can get out through the window

19:46.180 --> 19:48.180
Someone help me

19:48.180 --> 19:50.180
You okay, ma'am?

19:50.180 --> 19:51.180
I'm dying

19:51.180 --> 19:53.180
I have to get out of here

19:53.180 --> 19:55.180
Hey, ma'am, you be careful

19:55.180 --> 19:56.180
You're gonna fall

19:56.180 --> 19:57.180
Stop

19:57.180 --> 19:58.180
Stop!

20:02.180 --> 20:04.180
Someone get a doctor

20:04.180 --> 20:06.180
It's too late

20:06.180 --> 20:09.180
There ain't nothing a doctor can do now

20:13.180 --> 20:14.180
So

20:14.180 --> 20:16.180
She jumped from her balcony

20:16.180 --> 20:18.180
And now she's dead

20:18.180 --> 20:20.180
Are you sure that's what happened?

20:20.180 --> 20:21.180
Yes

20:21.180 --> 20:23.180
I came out of the room in house

20:23.180 --> 20:24.180
And I saw her

20:24.180 --> 20:26.180
Did anyone see you leave the room in house?

20:26.180 --> 20:27.180
No

20:27.180 --> 20:30.180
Everyone was looking at her lying dead in the street

20:30.180 --> 20:32.180
Oh, no

20:32.180 --> 20:34.180
I'm not sorry she's dead

20:34.180 --> 20:36.180
She was a bitch and a tramp

20:36.180 --> 20:38.180
But I didn't kill her

20:38.180 --> 20:43.180
I just feel that suddenly I have this power

20:43.180 --> 20:45.180
And I'm scared

20:45.180 --> 20:47.180
I don't want it

20:47.180 --> 20:49.180
Well, Marie

20:49.180 --> 20:52.180
This ain't something you can choose

20:52.180 --> 20:55.180
You don't go looking for this kind of power

20:55.180 --> 20:57.180
The power finds you

20:57.180 --> 21:00.180
Listen, you don't understand what's happening to you right now

21:00.180 --> 21:02.180
But I do

21:02.180 --> 21:04.180
You need help

21:04.180 --> 21:05.180
What kind of help?

21:05.180 --> 21:07.180
You need to come with me

21:07.180 --> 21:09.180
To plus Congo

21:09.180 --> 21:10.180
Plus Congo?

21:10.180 --> 21:12.180
I ain't going there

21:12.180 --> 21:13.180
It's too dangerous

21:13.180 --> 21:16.180
They're crazy people doing crazy stuff there

21:16.180 --> 21:19.180
Crazy dancing beating on drums

21:19.180 --> 21:21.180
I'm too scared to go there

21:21.180 --> 21:26.180
Marie is just a place where people go to worship the god they believe in

21:26.180 --> 21:28.180
I ain't going

21:28.180 --> 21:29.180
Okay

21:29.180 --> 21:31.180
But if you change your mind

21:31.180 --> 21:34.180
Meet me there on Sunday night

21:37.180 --> 21:39.180
Soon after Marie arrived home

21:39.180 --> 21:41.180
Jack walked through the door

21:42.180 --> 21:43.180
Marie

21:44.180 --> 21:45.180
Marie

21:45.180 --> 21:46.180
Where are you?

21:46.180 --> 21:47.180
I'm here

21:47.180 --> 21:48.180
In the pantry

21:48.180 --> 21:49.180
What do you want?

21:49.180 --> 21:52.180
What the hell do you think you're doing?

21:52.180 --> 21:54.180
I'm not doing anything, Jack

21:54.180 --> 21:57.180
I'm just sitting here minding my own business

21:57.180 --> 21:59.180
Minding your own business

21:59.180 --> 22:02.180
Is killing someone minding your own business

22:02.180 --> 22:04.180
What are you talking about, Jack?

22:04.180 --> 22:06.180
You know what I'm talking about

22:06.180 --> 22:07.180
Has someone died?

22:07.180 --> 22:09.180
You know damn well that someone has died

22:09.180 --> 22:11.180
Gina is dead

22:11.180 --> 22:12.180
Gina?

22:12.180 --> 22:16.180
Is that the woman I found you with at our wedding?

22:16.180 --> 22:18.180
You know who I'm talking about

22:18.180 --> 22:19.180
How did she die?

22:19.180 --> 22:21.180
Stop playing games with me Marie

22:21.180 --> 22:23.180
I ain't playing games, Jack

22:23.180 --> 22:25.180
Did she have an accident?

22:25.180 --> 22:26.180
No Marie

22:26.180 --> 22:28.180
She didn't have an accident

22:28.180 --> 22:35.180
Folks who were in the street say that she came out on her balcony screaming fit to wake in the dead

22:35.180 --> 22:40.180
She was yelling that someone was stabbing her with a knife

22:40.180 --> 22:42.180
Was someone stabbing her, Jack?

22:42.180 --> 22:44.180
No Marie

22:44.180 --> 22:46.180
No one was stabbing her

22:46.180 --> 22:49.180
But she thought someone was stabbing her

22:49.180 --> 22:50.180
And?

22:50.180 --> 22:53.180
And she threw herself off the balcony

22:53.180 --> 22:55.180
She's dead Marie

22:55.180 --> 22:59.180
And you expect me to feel sad about that?

22:59.180 --> 23:00.180
Listen to me

23:00.180 --> 23:03.180
No, Jack, you listen to me

23:03.180 --> 23:09.180
You wanted to go with that worthless tramp on our wedding day

23:09.180 --> 23:11.180
On our wedding day, Jack

23:11.180 --> 23:15.180
The day that should have been the most important day of my life

23:15.180 --> 23:17.180
And you ruined it all

23:17.180 --> 23:20.180
You didn't have to kill her

23:20.180 --> 23:23.180
Jack, I didn't lay a finger on that whore

23:23.180 --> 23:25.180
I'm glad she's dead

23:25.180 --> 23:27.180
It's what she deserves

23:27.180 --> 23:29.180
But I did not touch her

23:29.180 --> 23:31.180
You killed her

23:31.180 --> 23:33.180
You did it somehow

23:33.180 --> 23:34.180
I know you did

23:34.180 --> 23:38.180
And I ain't staying in the same house as you any longer

23:46.180 --> 23:47.180
John?

23:47.180 --> 23:50.180
Well Marie, nice to see you

23:50.180 --> 23:52.180
Welcome to Blast Congo

23:52.180 --> 23:54.180
What's going on here?

23:54.180 --> 23:55.180
It's scary

23:55.180 --> 23:59.180
It's just people having a good time Marie

23:59.180 --> 24:02.180
There ain't nothing to worry about

24:02.180 --> 24:04.180
Hey lady, come up there

24:04.180 --> 24:07.180
You tell her, Matthew, take your hands off me

24:07.180 --> 24:10.180
Oh, come now, lady, I ain't gonna hurt you

24:10.180 --> 24:13.180
You heard what the lady said, sir

24:13.180 --> 24:14.180
Oh yeah?

24:14.180 --> 24:16.180
And who the hell do you think you are?

24:16.180 --> 24:18.180
Hey, lay off, Matthew

24:18.180 --> 24:20.180
That's John Bayou

24:20.180 --> 24:22.180
John Bayou?

24:22.180 --> 24:23.180
Oh my God

24:23.180 --> 24:26.180
Dr. John, sorry, Mr. Bayou

24:26.180 --> 24:30.180
I think you better say sorry to the lady as well, so

24:30.180 --> 24:32.180
Sorry, lady

24:32.180 --> 24:34.180
Sorry I spoke to you

24:34.180 --> 24:35.180
Come on

24:35.180 --> 24:39.180
Well, John, you certainly have the power, too

24:39.180 --> 24:41.180
Maybe

24:42.180 --> 24:45.180
Anyway, you don't need to feel afraid

24:45.180 --> 24:48.180
I don't feel afraid when I'm with you

24:48.180 --> 24:50.180
But what's going on here?

24:50.180 --> 24:57.180
Well, most people here are just here to talk, dance, be with their friends

24:57.180 --> 25:00.180
But there's some religious stuff going on, too

25:00.180 --> 25:01.180
John?

25:01.180 --> 25:02.180
What is it?

25:02.180 --> 25:05.180
That man over there, the one near the fire

25:05.180 --> 25:07.180
What about him?

25:07.180 --> 25:10.180
He's dancing and he's holding a snake

25:10.180 --> 25:13.180
The snake is wrapped around his body

25:13.180 --> 25:14.180
That's right

25:14.180 --> 25:15.180
What's he doing?

25:15.180 --> 25:17.180
Don't worry, Marie

25:17.180 --> 25:19.180
He's a voodoo preacher

25:19.180 --> 25:23.180
Snicks are very special creatures to voodoo people

25:23.180 --> 25:25.180
But what's happening?

25:25.180 --> 25:27.180
The voodoo service is started

25:27.180 --> 25:29.180
And he afraid of the snake?

25:29.180 --> 25:32.180
No, Marie, he ain't afraid of the snake

25:32.180 --> 25:35.180
And you mustn't be afraid, either

25:35.180 --> 25:38.180
What do you mean, I mustn't be afraid?

25:38.180 --> 25:43.180
Marie, he may choose to give the snake to someone

25:43.180 --> 25:45.180
It's part of the service

25:45.180 --> 25:48.180
He may choose to give the snake to you

25:48.180 --> 25:51.180
Give me the snake, why?

25:51.180 --> 25:55.180
Don't be afraid if he asks you to take the snake

25:55.180 --> 25:58.180
Are you crazy? No way

25:58.180 --> 26:01.180
I'm not going anywhere near a snake

26:01.180 --> 26:03.180
Snake scare me to death

26:03.180 --> 26:07.180
Marie, you have nothing to fear from the snake

26:07.180 --> 26:10.180
You have the power to control you

26:10.180 --> 26:12.180
John, I can't do it

26:12.180 --> 26:14.180
I can't stay here

26:26.180 --> 26:29.180
Marie, there ain't no place you can go

26:29.180 --> 26:31.180
If the preacher wants to find you

26:31.180 --> 26:32.180
He'll find you

26:32.180 --> 26:34.180
Why are you saying this?

26:34.180 --> 26:37.180
You said I should come here to get help

26:37.180 --> 26:39.180
Then you'll scare me nearly to death

26:39.180 --> 26:41.180
Marie, trust me

26:41.180 --> 26:44.180
Why? Why should I trust you?

26:44.180 --> 26:47.180
3, 2, 3

26:49.020 --> 26:53.180
Rambalah widow

26:53.960 --> 26:56.180
Rambalah widow

26:56.180 --> 26:56.680
Rambalah widow

26:56.680 --> 26:58.680
Rambalah widow

26:58.680 --> 27:01.680
Rambalah widow

27:01.680 --> 27:04.180
From God's sake

27:04.180 --> 27:05.180
What'd she say?

27:05.180 --> 27:08.180
He's speaking to Rambalah widow

27:08.180 --> 27:10.180
Rambalah widow

27:10.180 --> 27:12.180
He's the voodoo snake God

27:12.180 --> 27:36.180
He is coming towards you, Mary.

27:36.180 --> 27:39.180
John, help me!

27:40.180 --> 27:44.180
Lady with the long black hair.

27:44.180 --> 27:46.180
What do you want?

27:46.180 --> 27:48.180
Take this name.

27:48.180 --> 27:50.180
No!

27:50.180 --> 27:52.180
Take this name!

27:52.180 --> 27:54.180
Take this name!

27:54.180 --> 27:56.180
Take this name!

27:56.180 --> 27:57.180
Take this name!

27:57.180 --> 27:59.180
Take this name!

27:59.180 --> 28:00.180
Take this name!

28:00.180 --> 28:02.180
Oh my God!

28:02.180 --> 28:04.180
Feel the power, Mary!

28:04.180 --> 28:06.180
You have the power!

28:06.180 --> 28:08.180
And the power will save you!

28:08.180 --> 28:10.180
Take it!

28:10.180 --> 28:12.180
Stop!

28:16.180 --> 28:18.180
Good, Mary!

28:18.180 --> 28:20.180
You're right.

28:20.180 --> 28:22.180
Mary!

28:22.180 --> 28:24.180
Dambala widow.

28:24.180 --> 28:27.180
Dambala widow.

28:27.180 --> 28:29.180
I hear you.

28:29.180 --> 28:32.180
I hear you!

28:32.180 --> 28:34.180
Dambala widow!

28:34.180 --> 28:36.180
Dambala widow!

28:44.180 --> 28:47.180
Mary left Place Congo a changed woman.

28:47.180 --> 28:52.180
The next day she received a visitor.

28:52.180 --> 28:56.180
Hold on.

28:56.180 --> 29:01.180
Okay, okay, I'm coming.

29:01.180 --> 29:03.180
Can I help you?

29:03.180 --> 29:05.180
Are you, Marie LaVoe?

29:05.180 --> 29:07.180
Maybe.

29:07.180 --> 29:08.180
Who wants to know?

29:08.180 --> 29:10.180
Let me in.

29:10.180 --> 29:12.180
Excuse me.

29:12.180 --> 29:13.180
Did I say you could come in?

29:13.180 --> 29:15.180
I have something to tell you.

29:15.180 --> 29:16.180
You do?

29:16.180 --> 29:17.180
Yes.

29:17.180 --> 29:20.180
I run the church for freed slaves.

29:20.180 --> 29:22.180
My name is Daddy.

29:22.180 --> 29:25.180
Some people call me Sanity Daddy.

29:25.180 --> 29:27.180
Aha!

29:27.180 --> 29:30.180
So you're Sanity Day Day.

29:30.180 --> 29:32.180
The voodoo queen.

29:32.180 --> 29:34.180
Well, well, well.

29:34.180 --> 29:39.180
So, why are you visiting Marie LaVoe?

29:39.180 --> 29:41.180
I guess you don't want me to cut your hair.

29:41.180 --> 29:44.180
Don't you make fun of me woman?

29:44.180 --> 29:46.180
Close the door.

29:46.180 --> 29:50.180
I heard about what you did last night in Place Congo.

29:50.180 --> 29:52.180
Is that right?

29:52.180 --> 29:57.180
People are talking about you as if you're the voodoo queen of New Orleans.

29:57.180 --> 29:58.180
They are.

29:58.180 --> 29:59.180
They are.

29:59.180 --> 30:01.180
And you ain't.

30:01.180 --> 30:04.180
Is that all you've come to tell me?

30:04.180 --> 30:09.180
If it is, then maybe you'd listen to me woman.

30:09.180 --> 30:11.180
And listen good.

30:11.180 --> 30:15.180
I heard you did something really bad.

30:15.180 --> 30:16.180
Really?

30:16.180 --> 30:17.180
Yes.

30:17.180 --> 30:21.180
I heard you killed a woman called Gina Baptiste.

30:23.180 --> 30:24.180
See?

30:24.180 --> 30:26.180
Now you know you're in trouble.

30:27.180 --> 30:32.180
I think you don't want to believe everything you hear.

30:32.180 --> 30:34.180
This Gina woman.

30:34.180 --> 30:36.180
She was messing with your husband right.

30:36.180 --> 30:37.180
That's enough.

30:37.180 --> 30:40.180
I don't want you in my house anymore.

30:40.180 --> 30:41.180
Get out of here.

30:41.180 --> 30:42.180
Listen.

30:42.180 --> 30:45.180
You're the one that needs to get out.

30:45.180 --> 30:48.180
It's time for you to pack your bags and leave town.

30:48.180 --> 30:50.180
Leave town?

30:50.180 --> 30:53.180
I ain't going nowhere.

30:53.180 --> 30:57.180
Leave town or you're going to die.

30:57.180 --> 31:01.180
You don't scare me one little bit.

31:01.180 --> 31:02.180
Listen woman.

31:02.180 --> 31:04.180
I'm getting tired of all of this.

31:04.180 --> 31:06.180
I'm going to give you one more chance.

31:06.180 --> 31:10.180
I'm giving you 24 hours to get out of here and go someplace else.

31:10.180 --> 31:16.180
And if I don't, if you don't, I'm going to the sheriff's office.

31:16.180 --> 31:22.180
And I'm going to tell a sheriff that I know who killed Gina Baptiste.

31:22.180 --> 31:24.180
Oh, come on.

31:24.180 --> 31:27.180
Is that the best you can do?

31:27.180 --> 31:30.180
That little piece of scum killed herself.

31:30.180 --> 31:33.180
Either that or it was an accident.

31:33.180 --> 31:34.180
Everyone knows that.

31:34.180 --> 31:38.180
She either jumped off her balcony or she fell.

31:38.180 --> 31:41.180
There are plenty of witnesses who can testify to that.

31:41.180 --> 31:43.180
Witnesses, huh?

31:43.180 --> 31:44.180
Yeah.

31:44.180 --> 31:46.180
Lots of people saw her.

31:46.180 --> 31:49.180
And you think that's what they're going to say in court?

31:49.180 --> 31:53.180
When you appear in court on trial for murder.

31:53.180 --> 31:58.180
Because when I tell a sheriff that you did it, you're going to be tried.

31:58.180 --> 32:01.180
And you can bring all the witnesses you like.

32:01.180 --> 32:03.180
They ain't going to save you.

32:03.180 --> 32:05.180
Is that right?

32:05.180 --> 32:07.180
And how do you know that?

32:07.180 --> 32:11.180
Because they're going to say what I tell them to say.

32:11.180 --> 32:17.180
They're going to say they saw you attack Gina Baptiste with a knife.

32:17.180 --> 32:20.180
And then you'll be tried.

32:20.180 --> 32:22.180
Convicted.

32:22.180 --> 32:24.180
And hanged.

32:24.180 --> 32:26.180
I told you.

32:26.180 --> 32:30.180
You don't scare me one bit.

32:30.180 --> 32:33.180
So you ain't going to leave.

32:33.180 --> 32:35.180
Too right I ain't going to leave.

32:35.180 --> 32:37.180
I'm staying right here.

32:37.180 --> 32:43.180
Well, you can't say I didn't give you a chance.

32:43.180 --> 32:47.180
I guess you have about 30 minutes before they come and get you.

32:47.180 --> 32:50.180
It's your last 30 minutes of freedom.

32:50.180 --> 32:51.180
And joy them.

32:51.180 --> 32:52.180
Wait.

32:52.180 --> 32:53.180
What?

32:53.180 --> 32:55.180
Come back in here.

32:55.180 --> 32:56.180
So.

32:56.180 --> 32:59.180
Changed your mind, have you?

32:59.180 --> 33:01.180
I said.

33:01.180 --> 33:03.180
Come back in here.

33:03.180 --> 33:04.180
Good.

33:04.180 --> 33:06.180
You finally come to your...

33:06.180 --> 33:09.180
What the hell do you think you're doing?

33:09.180 --> 33:12.180
You dare to hit me.

33:12.180 --> 33:17.180
Well, sister, you are in real trouble now.

33:17.180 --> 33:22.180
You just listen to me, you old witch.

33:22.180 --> 33:26.180
You only have power over people because they're afraid of you.

33:26.180 --> 33:27.180
That's all.

33:27.180 --> 33:30.180
But I ain't afraid of you.

33:30.180 --> 33:32.180
Not one bit.

33:32.180 --> 33:37.180
You don't scare me and there's nothing you can do to me.

33:37.180 --> 33:40.180
You're making a big mistake.

33:40.180 --> 33:41.180
Really?

33:41.180 --> 33:42.180
Okay.

33:42.180 --> 33:43.180
Try me.

33:43.180 --> 33:45.180
Go to the sheriff's office.

33:45.180 --> 33:46.180
I will.

33:46.180 --> 33:51.180
You're a dead woman, Marilla Vogue.

33:51.180 --> 33:53.180
Don't say I didn't warn you.

33:53.180 --> 33:57.180
You still have time to leave town.

33:57.180 --> 34:01.180
I don't need to leave town today.

34:01.180 --> 34:06.180
All I need to do is think about you.

34:11.180 --> 34:18.180
Sanite dei dei, walk quickly down the street, pushing people out of her way.

34:18.180 --> 34:20.180
Hey, lady, what's the hurry?

34:20.180 --> 34:22.180
Get out of my way.

34:22.180 --> 34:23.180
What was that?

34:23.180 --> 34:24.180
Leave it, Jake.

34:24.180 --> 34:25.180
Leave it.

