What? What is it, Henry?

55:01.180 --> 55:05.180
Margaret, we are in deep trouble.

55:05.180 --> 55:07.180
Why? What's happened?

55:07.180 --> 55:10.180
I... I have lost a lot of money.

55:10.180 --> 55:15.180
How much? A lot. How much?

55:15.180 --> 55:17.180
Ten thousand dollars.

55:17.180 --> 55:25.180
Ten... You lost ten thousand dollars? I didn't know you had ten thousand dollars.

55:25.180 --> 55:29.180
I didn't. I borrowed the money, and then I lost every cent.

55:29.180 --> 55:31.180
But how?

55:31.180 --> 55:38.180
I went into a land deal with a man. A terrible man called George Andrews, the man who was here this afternoon.

55:38.180 --> 55:41.180
That ugly little fat guy?

55:41.180 --> 55:47.180
Yes. He's a lawyer. And he's a crook. He stole all the money.

55:47.180 --> 55:52.180
Okay, so he committed a crime. Go tell a sheriff.

55:52.180 --> 56:02.180
Do that. The deal wasn't completely legal. I didn't realize it at the time. I... I guess I didn't read the small print in the contract.

56:02.180 --> 56:08.180
Henry, what are we going to do? This house isn't even worth ten thousand dollars.

56:08.180 --> 56:11.180
There is... a solution.

56:11.180 --> 56:13.180
What's that?

56:13.180 --> 56:17.180
Andrews will pay me the money back and pay off all my other debts.

56:17.180 --> 56:19.180
And why would he do that?

56:19.180 --> 56:24.180
Well, first of all, he has agreed to buy the land we own out west of the city.

56:24.180 --> 56:28.180
That piece of land near the Achavelia swamp?

56:28.180 --> 56:29.180
Yes.

56:29.180 --> 56:36.180
He wants to buy that land for ten thousand dollars? That's great!

56:36.180 --> 56:40.180
Not exactly. There's something else that he wants.

56:40.180 --> 56:41.180
What?

56:41.180 --> 56:42.180
Well...

56:42.180 --> 56:46.180
Henry, what is it that he wants?

56:46.180 --> 56:49.180
This afternoon, he met Leverne.

56:49.180 --> 56:50.180
And?

56:50.180 --> 56:56.180
He... well, he has asked me for her hand in marriage.

56:56.180 --> 57:00.180
What? Henry, Leverne is nineteen.

57:00.180 --> 57:02.180
Well, yes.

57:02.180 --> 57:05.180
And he is old and fat and disgusting.

57:05.180 --> 57:11.180
Henry, I am not going to allow that horrible man to marry my daughter.

57:11.180 --> 57:15.180
Margaret, things aren't as simple as that.

57:15.180 --> 57:16.180
I'll explain.

57:16.180 --> 57:18.180
The thing is...

57:24.180 --> 57:26.180
Can I come in?

57:26.180 --> 57:27.180
Yes.

57:27.180 --> 57:30.180
Margaret, what's the matter?

57:30.180 --> 57:33.180
I just heard some terrible news.

57:33.180 --> 57:35.180
What? What's happened?

57:35.180 --> 57:38.180
Henry just told me that someone wants to marry Leverne.

57:38.180 --> 57:41.180
You mean the young man who works on the sugar boat?

57:41.180 --> 57:43.180
No, Marie. Not Tom.

57:43.180 --> 57:47.180
A horrible old man called George Andrews.

57:47.180 --> 57:51.180
George Andrews? Yes.

57:51.180 --> 57:53.180
I'm an attorney at law.

57:53.180 --> 57:57.180
I'm advising Mr. Paris on his claim to have for your estate.

57:57.180 --> 57:58.180
Why?

57:58.180 --> 58:01.180
You son of a bitch.

58:09.180 --> 58:12.180
Yes, he's a disgusting little man.

58:12.180 --> 58:15.180
I know George Andrews.

58:15.180 --> 58:17.180
You do? Yes.

58:17.180 --> 58:21.180
In that case, you will understand why I'm so upset.

58:21.180 --> 58:26.180
You can't let that happen, Margaret. You cannot let that happen.

58:26.180 --> 58:28.180
Do you think I want it to happen?

58:28.180 --> 58:30.180
If you don't want it, don't allow it.

58:30.180 --> 58:33.180
It isn't as easy as that, Marie.

58:33.180 --> 58:35.180
We're in deep trouble.

58:35.180 --> 58:39.180
Henry owes money to this man a lot of money.

58:39.180 --> 58:42.180
Andrews can ruin us if he wants to.

58:42.180 --> 58:43.180
How?

58:43.180 --> 58:47.180
When he asked Henry for permission to speak to Leverne about marriage,

58:47.180 --> 58:49.180
Henry said no.

58:49.180 --> 58:52.180
So Andrews asked him to think again,

58:52.180 --> 58:55.180
and he said if Henry still said no,

58:55.180 --> 58:59.180
he was going to ask for all the money that Henry owes him.

58:59.180 --> 59:01.180
How much does he owe him?

59:01.180 --> 59:03.180
$10,000.

59:03.180 --> 59:05.180
Oh, my God.

59:05.180 --> 59:08.180
If we have to pay him, we'll have nothing.

59:08.180 --> 59:11.180
No house, no business, nothing.

59:11.180 --> 59:13.180
We'll be out on the street.

59:13.180 --> 59:15.180
Oh, Margaret.

59:15.180 --> 59:17.180
But if we agree to the marriage,

59:17.180 --> 59:21.180
Andrews will pay off all Henry's other debts as well.

59:21.180 --> 59:24.180
And he will also buy a useless piece of land that we own

59:24.180 --> 59:26.180
out near the Atchifu lion swamp.

59:26.180 --> 59:27.180
I see.

59:27.180 --> 59:30.180
I wish I could kill that man.

59:30.180 --> 59:33.180
But, you know, that wouldn't help.

59:33.180 --> 59:36.180
He has three children by his first marriage.

59:36.180 --> 59:38.180
To be clear of the dead.

59:38.180 --> 59:41.180
I would have to kill all of them as well.

59:41.180 --> 59:44.180
You know what the best thing would be?

59:44.180 --> 59:46.180
What's that, Margaret?

59:46.180 --> 59:48.180
Have Leverne marry him.

59:48.180 --> 59:50.180
And then kill him.

59:50.180 --> 59:55.180
You know, that ain't such a bad idea.

59:55.180 --> 59:58.180
That's a crazy idea, Margaret, and you know it.

59:58.180 --> 59:59.180
Marie?

59:59.180 --> 01:00:00.180
Yes.

01:00:00.180 --> 01:00:03.180
Could you do that for me?

01:00:04.180 --> 01:00:05.180
What?

01:00:05.180 --> 01:00:07.180
Kill a man.

01:00:07.180 --> 01:00:09.180
Margaret, are you out of your mind?

01:00:09.180 --> 01:00:12.180
Don't be all surprised with me, Marie.

01:00:12.180 --> 01:00:14.180
I know about the things that you do.

01:00:14.180 --> 01:00:16.180
What are you talking about?

01:00:16.180 --> 01:00:19.180
What are you talking about?

01:00:19.180 --> 01:00:22.180
You know, darn well what I'm talking about, Marie.

01:00:22.180 --> 01:00:24.180
I know about you.

01:00:24.180 --> 01:00:28.180
And all of those voodoo ceremonies down in Congo Square.

01:00:28.180 --> 01:00:30.180
Marie?

01:00:31.180 --> 01:00:33.180
Are you listening to me?

01:00:33.180 --> 01:00:34.180
I'm listening.

01:00:34.180 --> 01:00:36.180
Will you help me?

01:00:36.180 --> 01:00:40.180
Margaret, I don't normally work for white people.

01:00:40.180 --> 01:00:41.180
You don't, huh?

01:00:41.180 --> 01:00:43.180
Well, you're going to start now.

01:00:43.180 --> 01:00:45.180
Okay, Margaret.

01:00:45.180 --> 01:00:47.180
I'll try to help.

01:00:47.180 --> 01:00:49.180
You know I'd do anything for you.

01:00:49.180 --> 01:00:50.180
And...

01:00:50.180 --> 01:00:51.180
And what?

01:00:51.180 --> 01:00:54.180
I just remembered something.

01:00:54.180 --> 01:00:59.180
Something that George Andrews said to me just before Jack died.

01:01:00.180 --> 01:01:05.180
Mrs. Paris, since the day of your marriage to Mr. Paris, he has been legally entitled

01:01:05.180 --> 01:01:09.180
to one half by your estate.

01:01:09.180 --> 01:01:11.180
I have an idea.

01:01:11.180 --> 01:01:16.180
I think I know what we can do.

01:01:16.180 --> 01:01:17.180
Mother!

01:01:17.180 --> 01:01:18.180
Laverne.

01:01:18.180 --> 01:01:21.180
Father just told me the most terrible thing.

01:01:21.180 --> 01:01:24.180
He wants me to marry Mr. Andrews.

01:01:24.180 --> 01:01:25.180
I know.

01:01:25.180 --> 01:01:27.180
I won't do it, Mother.

01:01:27.180 --> 01:01:31.180
I'd rather cut my own throat than let that man touch me.

01:01:31.180 --> 01:01:33.180
Laverne, calm down.

01:01:33.180 --> 01:01:34.180
Calm down.

01:01:34.180 --> 01:01:35.180
Calm down.

01:01:35.180 --> 01:01:38.180
Mother, I won't do it.

01:01:38.180 --> 01:01:43.180
I love you and I love Dad, but I will not marry that man.

01:01:43.180 --> 01:01:46.180
The very thought of it makes me sick.

01:01:46.180 --> 01:01:48.180
Laverne, please.

01:01:48.180 --> 01:01:50.180
Just stop for a moment and listen to Marie.

01:01:50.180 --> 01:01:52.180
Listen to Marie.

01:01:52.180 --> 01:01:53.180
What for?

01:01:53.180 --> 01:01:54.180
Laverne.

01:01:55.180 --> 01:01:58.180
Just sit down for a moment and let me talk to you.

01:01:58.180 --> 01:02:00.180
I can help you.

01:02:00.180 --> 01:02:01.180
How?

01:02:01.180 --> 01:02:03.180
What can you do?

01:02:03.180 --> 01:02:05.180
If you marry this man.

01:02:05.180 --> 01:02:06.180
Marie, stop it.

01:02:06.180 --> 01:02:08.180
I don't want to hear it.

01:02:08.180 --> 01:02:09.180
Laverne.

01:02:09.180 --> 01:02:12.180
Quit squawking and hear me out.

01:02:12.180 --> 01:02:14.180
Sorry.

01:02:14.180 --> 01:02:16.180
In fact, it is Laverne.

01:02:16.180 --> 01:02:18.180
You only have to marry him.

01:02:18.180 --> 01:02:23.180
Go through with the wedding and you will immediately inherit half of his estate.

01:02:23.180 --> 01:02:24.180
And?

01:02:24.180 --> 01:02:25.180
And then will.

01:02:25.180 --> 01:02:27.180
I'll tell Marie.

01:02:27.180 --> 01:02:31.180
If you don't marry Andrews, we will lose everything.

01:02:31.180 --> 01:02:35.180
The house, the business, everything.

01:02:35.180 --> 01:02:38.180
Why didn't anyone tell me?

01:02:38.180 --> 01:02:41.180
Laverne, I didn't know about it until today either.

01:02:41.180 --> 01:02:44.180
Well, you two, listen to my plan.

01:02:44.180 --> 01:02:45.180
Sorry.

01:02:45.180 --> 01:02:47.180
Laverne.

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:52.180
As soon as you are married to Mr. Andrews, I will make sure that,

01:02:52.180 --> 01:02:55.180
something happens to him.

01:02:55.180 --> 01:02:56.180
What?

01:02:56.180 --> 01:02:59.180
What's going to happen to him?

01:02:59.180 --> 01:03:01.180
Trust me, Laverne.

01:03:01.180 --> 01:03:04.180
He won't be a problem for you.

01:03:04.180 --> 01:03:06.180
But I need your help.

01:03:06.180 --> 01:03:11.180
You must go to Mr. Andrews' house and you must agree to marry him.

01:03:11.180 --> 01:03:14.180
Marie, I can't do that.

01:03:14.180 --> 01:03:16.180
I rarely can't.

01:03:16.180 --> 01:03:17.180
Hear me out.

01:03:17.180 --> 01:03:19.180
Agree to marry him.

01:03:19.180 --> 01:03:23.180
And bring me back something that belongs to him.

01:03:23.180 --> 01:03:25.180
What kind of thing?

01:03:25.180 --> 01:03:28.180
The simplest thing would be a handkerchief.

01:03:28.180 --> 01:03:31.180
Look, Margaret, I have to go now.

01:03:31.180 --> 01:03:33.180
But I'll be back later.

01:03:33.180 --> 01:03:35.180
Trust me, Laverne.

01:03:35.180 --> 01:03:38.180
Everything will be okay.

01:03:38.180 --> 01:03:41.180
Mama, why am I agreeing to this?

01:03:41.180 --> 01:03:45.180
I can't bear the idea of that man touching me.

01:03:45.180 --> 01:03:49.180
I deliver and trust Marie.

01:03:49.180 --> 01:03:51.180
She knows what she's doing.

01:03:51.180 --> 01:03:53.180
You'd better be right.

01:03:53.180 --> 01:03:59.180
Because if I have to live with that man, I'm going to kill myself.

01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:08.180
The next morning, Henry Salinger and his daughter Laverne visited George Andrews.

01:04:08.180 --> 01:04:11.180
Henry, hello George.

01:04:11.180 --> 01:04:13.180
So good to see you.

01:04:13.180 --> 01:04:14.180
Laverne.

01:04:14.180 --> 01:04:16.180
Hello, Mr. Andrews.

01:04:16.180 --> 01:04:21.180
Boy, Laverne, you look good enough to eat.

01:04:21.180 --> 01:04:23.180
Can we come in, George?

01:04:23.180 --> 01:04:25.180
A short thing, Henry.

01:04:25.180 --> 01:04:26.180
Come in.

01:04:26.180 --> 01:04:30.180
George, we've come to talk about your proposal.

01:04:30.180 --> 01:04:31.180
Good.

01:04:31.180 --> 01:04:34.180
And I hope you agree it's a good idea.

01:04:34.180 --> 01:04:38.180
Because if you haven't, then it's the end of the road for the Salinger's.

01:04:39.180 --> 01:04:43.180
Well, yes, Laverne has agreed to marry you.

01:04:43.180 --> 01:04:46.180
What did you do, Laverne?

01:04:46.180 --> 01:04:49.180
You just made the best decision of your life.

01:04:49.180 --> 01:04:50.180
Come here.

01:04:50.180 --> 01:04:51.180
Oh, Mr. Andrews.

01:04:51.180 --> 01:04:55.180
George, please, can we just discuss a few details?

01:04:55.180 --> 01:04:57.180
It's okay, Laverne.

01:04:57.180 --> 01:05:00.180
I can wait, but not for long.

01:05:00.180 --> 01:05:04.180
Let me get you folks a drink to celebrate.

01:05:05.180 --> 01:05:08.180
George, it's 11 o'clock in the morning.

01:05:08.180 --> 01:05:11.180
Isn't it kind of early to be drinking?

01:05:11.180 --> 01:05:13.180
Not when there's something like this to celebrate.

01:05:13.180 --> 01:05:14.180
No, George.

01:05:14.180 --> 01:05:15.180
I think...

01:05:15.180 --> 01:05:16.180
Oh, no, Dad.

01:05:16.180 --> 01:05:18.180
I think that's a nice idea.

01:05:18.180 --> 01:05:22.180
My father would like to join you, Mr. Andrews.

01:05:22.180 --> 01:05:23.180
Good.

01:05:23.180 --> 01:05:26.180
Well, I'm glad she has more sense than you, Henry.

01:05:26.180 --> 01:05:28.180
Even if she is just a woman.

01:05:28.180 --> 01:05:30.180
Hey, hold on there.

01:05:30.180 --> 01:05:33.180
And I'll be back with some bourbon.

01:05:34.180 --> 01:05:37.180
Laverne, what are you thinking about?

01:05:37.180 --> 01:05:38.180
Don't worry, Dad.

01:05:38.180 --> 01:05:39.180
I know what I'm doing.

01:05:39.180 --> 01:05:41.180
You know that I don't drink in the morning.

01:05:41.180 --> 01:05:43.180
Well, you're gonna have to start, Dad.

01:05:43.180 --> 01:05:47.180
I want you to accept a glass of bourbon from Mr. Andrews.

01:05:47.180 --> 01:05:48.180
And then...

01:05:48.180 --> 01:05:49.180
Here we are.

01:05:49.180 --> 01:05:51.180
A bottle of my best bourbon.

01:05:51.180 --> 01:05:53.180
It's 15 years old.

01:05:53.180 --> 01:05:57.180
Henry, have you any idea how much this stuff costs?

01:05:57.180 --> 01:05:58.180
No, George.

01:05:58.180 --> 01:06:00.180
I don't know how much it costs.

01:06:00.180 --> 01:06:02.180
Don't you want to know how much it costs?

01:06:03.180 --> 01:06:06.180
How much does it cost, George?

01:06:06.180 --> 01:06:09.180
This beauty is $7 a bottle.

01:06:09.180 --> 01:06:12.180
$7, but worth every cent.

01:06:12.180 --> 01:06:15.180
I have about 60 bottles of it in the cellar.

01:06:15.180 --> 01:06:18.180
Can I see the bottle, Mr. Andrews?

01:06:18.180 --> 01:06:20.180
Oh, why, yes, Laverne.

01:06:20.180 --> 01:06:21.180
Thank you.

01:06:21.180 --> 01:06:26.180
Well, Laverne, I didn't think you would be a bourbon drinker.

01:06:26.180 --> 01:06:28.180
Let me pour you a glass.

01:06:28.180 --> 01:06:29.180
Oh, no.

01:06:29.180 --> 01:06:31.180
I don't want to drink it, Mr. Andrews.

01:06:31.180 --> 01:06:35.180
I'm just interested in... in bottles.

01:06:35.180 --> 01:06:36.180
Oh!

01:06:36.180 --> 01:06:37.180
Be careful.

01:06:39.180 --> 01:06:40.180
Laverne.

01:06:40.180 --> 01:06:42.180
Oh, my God.

01:06:42.180 --> 01:06:44.180
That table is worth a fortune.

01:06:44.180 --> 01:06:47.180
I'm so sorry, Mr. Andrews.

01:06:47.180 --> 01:06:49.180
Let me clear up the glass.

01:06:49.180 --> 01:06:51.180
Don't be ridiculous, Laverne.

01:06:51.180 --> 01:06:54.180
I have servants to do this kind of stuff.

01:06:54.180 --> 01:06:55.180
Martha!

01:06:55.180 --> 01:06:56.180
No, no.

01:06:56.180 --> 01:06:57.180
I broke it.

01:06:57.180 --> 01:06:59.180
I want to clear it up.

01:06:59.180 --> 01:07:00.180
No, no, Laverne.

01:07:00.180 --> 01:07:01.180
Stop it.

01:07:01.180 --> 01:07:02.180
Get up off the floor.

01:07:02.180 --> 01:07:04.180
It's okay, Mr. Andrews.

01:07:04.180 --> 01:07:06.180
Here, take this piece.

01:07:06.180 --> 01:07:07.180
Gah!

01:07:07.180 --> 01:07:09.180
Laverne, careful.

01:07:09.180 --> 01:07:11.180
You just cut Mr. Andrews' hand.

01:07:11.180 --> 01:07:14.180
Jesus Christ, I'm bleeding to death.

01:07:14.180 --> 01:07:15.180
Martha!

01:07:15.180 --> 01:07:16.180
Oh, no.

01:07:16.180 --> 01:07:18.180
I'm so sorry.

01:07:18.180 --> 01:07:20.180
Quick, let me help you.

01:07:20.180 --> 01:07:24.180
Sit down here and give me a handkerchief.

01:07:24.180 --> 01:07:25.180
I...

01:07:25.180 --> 01:07:28.180
I'll use this one in your top pocket.

01:07:28.180 --> 01:07:30.180
It's okay, Dad.

01:07:30.180 --> 01:07:32.180
Mr. Andrews won't mind.

01:07:32.180 --> 01:07:34.180
Martha, where are you?

01:07:34.180 --> 01:07:36.180
I'm right here, Mr. Andrews.

01:07:36.180 --> 01:07:37.180
Oh, my goodness.

01:07:37.180 --> 01:07:39.180
What have you done to your hand?

01:07:39.180 --> 01:07:41.180
What have I done to my hand?

01:07:41.180 --> 01:07:43.180
You can see with your own eyes.

01:07:43.180 --> 01:07:45.180
I'm bleeding to death.

01:07:45.180 --> 01:07:47.180
Come with me into the pantry, Mr. Andrews.

01:07:47.180 --> 01:07:49.180
I'll clean that up.

01:07:49.180 --> 01:07:53.180
We'll come back later, George, when things have calmed down a little.

01:07:59.180 --> 01:08:05.180
Later that day, Laverne took Mr. Andrews' silk handkerchief to Marie's house.

01:08:05.180 --> 01:08:07.180
I got this, Marie.

01:08:07.180 --> 01:08:09.180
Well done, Laverne.

01:08:09.180 --> 01:08:11.180
How come it's covered in blood?

01:08:11.180 --> 01:08:16.180
I dropped a seven dollar bottle of bourbon on a glass coffee table.

01:08:16.180 --> 01:08:18.180
There was glass everywhere.

01:08:18.180 --> 01:08:24.180
Then I accidentally cut Mr. Andrews' hand with a piece of broken glass.

01:08:24.180 --> 01:08:25.180
My.

01:08:25.180 --> 01:08:27.180
I really enjoyed it.

01:08:28.180 --> 01:08:29.180
Oh, my God.

01:08:29.180 --> 01:08:30.180
What am I saying?

01:08:30.180 --> 01:08:31.180
I understand.

01:08:31.180 --> 01:08:34.180
What are you going to do with it?

01:08:34.180 --> 01:08:35.180
Look at this.

01:08:35.180 --> 01:08:37.180
The doll?

01:08:37.180 --> 01:08:38.180
What about it?

01:08:38.180 --> 01:08:42.180
Laverne, this is going to save your life.

01:08:42.180 --> 01:08:45.180
But it's just a doll.

01:08:45.180 --> 01:08:46.180
Yes.

01:08:46.180 --> 01:08:50.180
And I'm going to put the handkerchief around the doll.

01:08:50.180 --> 01:08:51.180
Like this.

01:08:52.180 --> 01:08:54.180
And?

01:08:54.180 --> 01:08:57.180
How does that help, Anderson?

01:08:57.180 --> 01:09:03.180
Laverne, it means I can do something to Mr. Andrews.

01:09:03.180 --> 01:09:05.180
Anytime I want.

01:09:05.180 --> 01:09:07.180
What do you mean?

01:09:07.180 --> 01:09:09.180
Do something.

01:09:09.180 --> 01:09:11.180
Watch.

01:09:11.180 --> 01:09:16.180
First of all, I just put this needle into the doll.

01:09:16.180 --> 01:09:19.180
Like this?

01:09:19.180 --> 01:09:24.180
And Mr. Andrews is going to get a sharp pain.

01:09:24.180 --> 01:09:25.180
Right there.

01:09:25.180 --> 01:09:29.180
In his chest.

01:09:29.180 --> 01:09:32.180
Mother, do you know where to...

01:09:32.180 --> 01:09:35.180
What's the matter, Mr. Andrews?

01:09:35.180 --> 01:09:36.180
Nothing.

01:09:36.180 --> 01:09:37.180
I just...

01:09:37.180 --> 01:09:39.180
You okay?

01:09:39.180 --> 01:09:41.180
Sit down for a moment.

01:09:41.180 --> 01:09:45.180
I just got a pain here in my chest.

01:09:45.180 --> 01:09:46.180
It's okay.

01:09:46.180 --> 01:09:47.180
It's gone now.

01:09:47.180 --> 01:09:50.180
Mr. Andrews, when are you going to take my advice

01:09:50.180 --> 01:09:52.180
and stop drinking so much bourbon?

01:09:52.180 --> 01:09:54.180
Never, Martha, never.

01:09:54.180 --> 01:09:57.180
I like bourbon too much to ever stop.

01:09:57.180 --> 01:10:19.180
A few weeks later, the wedding took place.

01:10:19.180 --> 01:10:24.180
After the church service, there was a big party in Andrews' house in Canal Street.

01:10:24.180 --> 01:10:29.180
Laverne was sick with worry.

01:10:29.180 --> 01:10:32.180
Congratulations, Laverne, and good luck.

01:10:32.180 --> 01:10:34.180
Thanks.

01:10:34.180 --> 01:10:40.180
My God, she needs all the luck she can get.

01:10:40.180 --> 01:10:41.180
Hello, Marie.

01:10:41.180 --> 01:10:43.180
Hi, Margaret.

01:10:43.180 --> 01:10:44.180
How are you feeling?

01:10:44.180 --> 01:10:45.180
Terrible.

01:10:45.180 --> 01:10:48.180
But there is some good news.

01:10:48.180 --> 01:10:52.180
Andrews has already paid off Henry's debts to all the banks in town.

01:10:52.180 --> 01:10:53.180
That's wonderful.

01:10:53.180 --> 01:10:54.180
Marie.

01:10:54.180 --> 01:10:55.180
Hi, Laverne.

01:10:55.180 --> 01:10:56.180
You look lovely.

01:10:56.180 --> 01:10:58.180
Marie, what's going on?

01:10:58.180 --> 01:11:00.180
You said everything would be okay.

01:11:00.180 --> 01:11:03.180
Well, it doesn't feel okay to me.

01:11:03.180 --> 01:11:04.180
Don't panic.

01:11:04.180 --> 01:11:09.180
It would be okay, I promise.

01:11:09.180 --> 01:11:15.180
Ladies and gentlemen, please raise your glasses for a toast to George and Laverne.

01:11:15.180 --> 01:11:18.180
George and Laverne.

01:11:19.180 --> 01:11:28.180
Marie, are you?

01:11:28.180 --> 01:11:30.180
Oh, where's Marie?

01:11:30.180 --> 01:11:33.180
Laverne, did you see where Marie went?

01:11:33.180 --> 01:11:34.180
No.

01:11:34.180 --> 01:11:38.180
No one knew where Marie was, but she was nearby.

01:11:38.180 --> 01:11:43.180
And she had the doll covered with the blood-stained silk handkerchief.

01:11:43.180 --> 01:11:46.180
And she had a sharp needle.

01:11:46.180 --> 01:11:49.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:11:49.180 --> 01:11:52.180
Hear my words.

01:11:52.180 --> 01:11:58.180
Now, ladies and gentlemen, pray silence for the groom, Mr. George Andrews.

01:12:06.180 --> 01:12:07.180
Thank you.

01:12:07.180 --> 01:12:08.180
Thank you very much.

01:12:08.180 --> 01:12:11.180
Well, I'm so glad that you could all come to my wedding.

01:12:11.180 --> 01:12:15.180
And I hope the food and drink are to your satisfaction.

01:12:15.180 --> 01:12:17.180
Well, they should be.

01:12:17.180 --> 01:12:20.180
This whole thing costs me a huge pile of money.

01:12:26.180 --> 01:12:28.180
And let's be honest.

01:12:28.180 --> 01:12:31.180
Money is what this is all about.

01:12:31.180 --> 01:12:33.180
I work hard all my life.

01:12:33.180 --> 01:12:35.180
I mean a lot of money.

01:12:35.180 --> 01:12:37.180
I mean a lot of money.

01:12:37.180 --> 01:12:40.180
And now I get my reward.

01:12:40.180 --> 01:12:42.180
I have a beautiful young bride and...

01:12:42.180 --> 01:12:44.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:12:44.180 --> 01:12:46.180
I...

01:12:46.180 --> 01:12:48.180
What was that?

01:12:48.180 --> 01:12:50.180
What was what, George?

01:12:50.180 --> 01:12:53.180
Voice kinda spooky voice.

01:12:53.180 --> 01:12:56.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:12:56.180 --> 01:12:57.180
That is again.

01:12:57.180 --> 01:12:59.180
Didn't anyone hear it?

01:12:59.180 --> 01:13:02.180
No one heard anything.

01:13:02.180 --> 01:13:04.180
You didn't hear a voice.

01:13:04.180 --> 01:13:06.180
Saying something foreign?

01:13:06.180 --> 01:13:07.180
No, George.

01:13:07.180 --> 01:13:10.180
The only voice we can hear is yours.

01:13:11.180 --> 01:13:13.180
Right.

01:13:13.180 --> 01:13:15.180
Well, as I was saying,

01:13:15.180 --> 01:13:18.180
I have a beautiful young bride.

01:13:18.180 --> 01:13:20.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:13:23.180 --> 01:13:25.180
George, you're right.

01:13:25.180 --> 01:13:27.180
Of course I'm all right.

01:13:27.180 --> 01:13:29.180
It's my wedding day.

01:13:29.180 --> 01:13:31.180
What was I saying?

01:13:31.180 --> 01:13:33.180
I have always believed

01:13:33.180 --> 01:13:35.180
that what you...

01:13:35.180 --> 01:13:36.180
You get what?

01:13:36.180 --> 01:13:38.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:13:39.180 --> 01:13:41.180
George, sit down, man.

01:13:41.180 --> 01:13:42.180
You look terrible.

01:13:42.180 --> 01:13:44.180
Leave me alone, damn you.

01:13:44.180 --> 01:13:46.180
This is my wedding party,

01:13:46.180 --> 01:13:48.180
which I have paid for.

01:13:48.180 --> 01:13:50.180
Most people would expect the bride's father

01:13:50.180 --> 01:13:52.180
to pay for all this,

01:13:52.180 --> 01:13:53.180
but he didn't.

01:13:53.180 --> 01:13:55.180
Dumb balla widow.

01:13:59.180 --> 01:14:01.180
Get out the way.

01:14:01.180 --> 01:14:03.180
Let him get some air.

01:14:03.180 --> 01:14:05.180
Oh, my God!

01:14:06.180 --> 01:14:08.180
George was dead.

01:14:08.180 --> 01:14:11.180
The doctor said he had a heart attack.

01:14:11.180 --> 01:14:13.180
All of her was a widow

01:14:13.180 --> 01:14:15.180
before her wedding day was over.

01:14:15.180 --> 01:14:18.180
But I guess inheriting $100,000 of charges

01:14:18.180 --> 01:14:21.180
money helped her to recover quickly.

01:14:21.180 --> 01:14:23.180
And Marie?

01:14:23.180 --> 01:14:26.180
Well, she was most definitely

01:14:26.180 --> 01:14:29.180
the queen in New Orleans.

